				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-513737#post-1494231</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-513737/on-the-seventh-day-of-christmas#post-1494231</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 29 Jun 2012 18:23:33 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>wishun</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1204404</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>woah, emotional whip-lash.<br /> Skip is stumbling-puppy cute for 99%. I really wanted him to catch that lizard, he was just trying so hard! A twig, a leaf, even air holes, what more could a gecko want?<br /> But then, in the space of about 2 sentences, Skip is suddenly Damien-staring-at-the-camera creepy. With an unknown, shadowy purpose; and all his antics are tainted with suspicion.<br /> That actually kind of spoils the fun of Skip for me, and I don't like it one bit.</p> <p>But I can't argue that this was some excellent writing, so I guess I have to +1.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
